Read **@AGENTS.md** at the repo root before working — it is the single source
of truth for this project (hard invariants, gates, layout, and the non-obvious
gotchas that make you fast).

Load-bearing rules (full detail in AGENTS.md):

- `src/rabbitkit/core/` must NOT import `pika` or `aio_pika`.
- One handler per queue (`DuplicateRouteError` otherwise).
- Before committing: `ruff check src/ tests/ benchmarks/`,
  `mypy src/rabbitkit/ --strict --ignore-missing-imports`, `pytest tests/unit/`.
- No `Co-Authored-By` trailers. Don't bump version unless asked.
